## `_to_entry_attributes(node_inode: int, node: NodeRow) -> pyfuse3.EntryAttributes`
<!-- checksum: adapter-2 -->

### Purpose
Translate a library `NodeRow` into a `pyfuse3.EntryAttributes` struct suitable for returning to the kernel. Stitches `kind` into the top bits of `st_mode` and computes `st_blocks` from `st_size`.

### Preconditions
- `node.kind` is one of `"file"`, `"dir"`, `"symlink"`.
- `node.mode` fits in 12 bits (mode bits only; we OR in the kind bits).

### Postconditions
- Returns an `EntryAttributes` with: `st_ino`, `st_nlink`, `st_size`, `st_mode` (mode | kind), `st_uid`, `st_gid`, `st_atime_ns`, `st_mtime_ns`, `st_ctime_ns`, `generation=0`, `entry_timeout=0`, `attr_timeout=0`, `st_blksize=4096`, `st_blocks=ceil(size/512)`.

### Implementation Notes

```python
def _to_entry_attributes(node_inode, node):
    ea = pyfuse3.EntryAttributes()
    ea.st_ino = node_inode
    ea.st_nlink = node.nlink
    ea.st_size = node.size
    ea.st_mode = (node.mode & 0o7777) | _KIND_TO_MODE_BITS[node.kind]
    ea.st_uid = node.uid
    ea.st_gid = node.gid
    ea.st_atime_ns = node.atime_ns
    ea.st_mtime_ns = node.mtime_ns
    ea.st_ctime_ns = node.ctime_ns
    ea.generation = 0
    ea.entry_timeout = 0
    ea.attr_timeout = 0
    ea.st_blksize = 4096
    ea.st_blocks = (node.size + 511) // 512
    return ea
```

